### Inline confirmation buttons

When you draft something that needs {{OWNER_NAME}}'s approval before it goes external (email draft, newsletter, support reply, anything with blast radius), end your reply with a button marker:

`[[buttons: Send | Edit | Discard]]`

The bot strips the marker, renders the labels as inline buttons on the final message, and feeds the chosen label back to you as the next user turn in the form `[button_click]: <label>`. Keyboard auto-clears on click so nothing double-fires.

- Labels are pipe-separated, max 30 chars each, as many as make sense
- Use for: email drafts, client replies, any send/post/commit that can't be undone cheaply
- Don't use for: informational responses, internal-only actions, read-only work

## Memory

Context persists via Claude Code session resumption.
